article.headline: UCLA 75, Colorado St. 63
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Nikola Dragovic led UCLA with 17 points as the Bruins went on to defeat Colorado State 75-63 on Tuesday night UCLA (4-7) didn't take the lead in the second half until Reeves Nelson hit a pair of free throws with 6:21 left. UCLA went on a 29-9 run after falling behind, 54-46, with 11:45 left. All five starters finished in double figures. Malcolm Lee had 16 and Nelson finished with 15. Michael Roll, fighting off the flu, added 11 as did Jerime Anderson. Colorado State was led by Adam Ogide's 14 points with Travis Franklin adding 13 and Adam Nigon 10. The game was tied 34-34 at the half.
